&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to gain paid experience in secure settings whilst undertaking your self-funded training as a Counselling Psychologist. Ideally you will be in your third year of training although candidates with considerable previous mental health experience and/or training may be considered in their second year of their doctoral level training. For more information please read the Job Description &amp; Service Specification. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Northamptonshire NHS Foundation Trust is a dynamic and forward thinking trust and good candidates in similar positions have in the past gone on to secure employment with the trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details please contact Ricky Rasmussen, Principal Counselling Psychologist at Ricky.rasmussen@nhft.nhs.uk or Sunil Lad, Consultant Counselling Psychologist on 07768803884&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
